<BlogPostLayout post={post}>
  <p class="key-takeaway">There is no single price for crawl space drainage in McDonough, GA. Cost is driven by how much drainage is needed, whether a sump pump is required, the soil and access under the home, and any exterior grading work. A short interior drain is a small project; a full perimeter system with a pump is a larger one. The reliable way to get a real number is a free inspection and a written estimate.</p>

  <p>If your crawl space collects water after Henry County's heavy summer storms, drainage is usually the first fix to budget for — and the one homeowners have the hardest time pricing online. That is because "crawl space drainage" can mean anything from redirecting a downspout to installing a full interior perimeter drain tied to a <a href="/wet-crawl-space-repair/">sump pump</a>. Below is how the cost actually breaks down so you can read an estimate with confidence.</p>

  <h2>What drives crawl space drainage cost?</h2>
  <p>Five factors do most of the work in setting the price. Understanding them helps you compare quotes and see why two homes on the same street can land at very different numbers.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Cost factor</th><th>Why it moves the price</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Linear footage of drainage</td><td>Longer perimeter drain runs and more collection points mean more material and labor — usually the biggest single driver.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Sump pump system</td><td>A pump, basin, and discharge line are a major add-on, included only when water has to be actively pumped out.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Soil and access</td><td>Trenching through dense Georgia red clay in a low-clearance crawl space is far slower than open, workable ground.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Exterior corrections</td><td>Regrading, downspout extensions, and gutter work add to the scope but reduce how much water arrives.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Discharge distance</td><td>Routing water far enough from the foundation to drain safely can add piping and labor.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Interior vs. exterior drainage</h2>
  <p>The two approaches solve different parts of the problem, and the right plan often uses both.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Interior drainage</strong> collects water that has already entered the crawl space — typically a perimeter drain that channels water to a sump pump, which discharges it away from the home. This is what handles water that gets in.</li>
    <li><strong>Exterior drainage</strong> reduces how much water reaches the foundation in the first place: regrading soil to slope away from the house, extending downspouts, and clearing gutters. It is often the more cost-effective starting point.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Why drainage is priced before encapsulation</h2>
  <p>If water regularly enters your crawl space, drainage should be installed before any <a href="/crawl-space-encapsulation/">encapsulation</a> or new <a href="/vapor-barrier-installation/">vapor barrier</a>. Sealing over an undrained space traps water beneath the liner, where it pools and undoes the work. Pricing drainage first means the sealed crawl space you pay for actually stays dry.</p>

  <h2>Local context: McDonough and Henry County</h2>
  <p>Henry County sits on dense red clay that absorbs water slowly. When a summer thunderstorm drops rain faster than the clay can take it, water pools against the foundation and works its way under the home through vents, cracks, and grading low spots. That is why <a href="/crawl-space-drainage/">crawl space drainage</a> is one of the most common — and most valuable — moisture investments for homes in McDonough, Stockbridge, Locust Grove, and the surrounding area.</p>

  <h2>How to get an accurate drainage estimate</h2>
  <p>Because the cost swing is so wide, an in-person inspection is the only way to price it honestly. During an estimate, ask where the water is entering, whether a sump pump is recommended, how far the discharge will run, and whether exterior grading should be corrected first. <a href="/contact/">Request a free crawl space inspection</a> and you will get a written scope that separates the must-haves from the optional upgrades.</p>
